  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cerebral infarction is a type of stroke that can lead to sometimes disabling sequelae. Among
      these sequelae, fatigue is frequently reported by patients. It is therefore important for
      doctors to understand why patients suffer from fatigue after cerebral infarction and to
      determine whether treatments given for the cerebral infarction may have an impact on this
      fatigue.

      The aim of this research was to study the frequency of fatigue after cerebral infarction, the
      associated factors, in particular the impact of treatments administered in the acute phase.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
